Problem Link: https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-subsequences-that-satisfy-the-given-sum-condition/description/

class Solution {
    public int numSubseq(int[] nums, int target) {
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        int numOfSubSeq = 0;
        int mod = 1000000007;
        int n = nums.length;

        int[] power = new int[n];
        power[0] = 1;
        for ( int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            power[i] = ( 2 * power[i-1] ) % mod;
        }

        int l = 0 ;
        int r = n-1;

        while ( l <= r ) {
            int sum = nums[l] + nums[r];
            if ( sum > target ) {
                r--;
            } else {
                numOfSubSeq = (numOfSubSeq + power[r-l]) % mod;
                l++;
            }
        }
    return numOfSubSeq;
    }
}


Approach:

1. Sort the Array
- Enables two-pointer technique to find valid min-max pairs efficiently.

2. Precompute Powers of 2

- Calculate power[i] = 2^i % mod to quickly determine the number of valid subsequences in any window.

Two-Pointer Technique

1. Initialize left = 0 (min) and right = n-1 (max).

2. For each window:
  If nums[left] + nums[right] ≤ target:
    All subsequences in this window are valid → add 2^(right-left) to result. -> ** We are not adding for full window size (r-l+1). This result only contains subsequences which have the leftmost element present in them. **
    Move left++ to explore larger minimums.
  Else:
    Move right-- to try smaller maximums.

Modulo Operation

Ensures results stay within bounds for large numbers.
